ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.250                Enzyme
NAME        D-inositol-3-phosphate glycosyltransferase;
            mycothiol glycosyltransferases;
            MshA
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine:1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate alpha-D-glycosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + 1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate = 1-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl)-1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate + UDP [RN:R09634]
ALL_REAC    R09634
SUBSTRATE   UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine [CPD:C00043];
            1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate [CPD:C04006]
PRODUCT     1-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl)-1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate [CPD:C19761];
            UDP [CPD:C00015]
COMMENT     The enzyme, which belongs to the GT-B fold superfamily, catalyses the first dedicated reaction in the biosynthesis of mycothiol [1]. The substrate was initially believed to be inositol, but eventually shown to be D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate [2]. A substantial conformational change occurs upon UDP binding, which generates the binding site for D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate [3].
